Name: DATA LINK TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: A 4- OR 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO LINK 11, LINK 11B OR LINK 16 DATA LINK UNITS AND TRACKS.

Name: DATA LINK TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 4- OR 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS USED IN LINK 11, LINK 11B OR LINK 16 DATA LINK OPERATIONS.

Name: DATA LINK TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 4- OR 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS USED IN LINK 11, LINK 11B OR LINK 16 DATA LINK OPERATIONS.

Name: AIRCRAFT TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: 2 ATAF TRACK NUMBERING CONVENTION.

Name: NATO TRACK NUMBER ROOT
Explanation: THE 2-CHARACTER ALPHABETIC PREFIX USED IN A LINK 1 TRACK NUMBER.

Name: LINK 1 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF UNIT ADDRESSES OR TRACK NUMBERS IN A LINK 1 TACTICAL DATA LINK.

Name: LINK 1 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF UNIT ADDRESSES OR TRACK NUMBERS IN A LINK 1 TACTICAL DATA LINK.

Name: LINK 1 REPORTING UNIT NUMBER
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE ASSIGNED AS A UNIT ADDRESS IN A LINK 1 TACTICAL DATA LINK.

Name: ATDL-1 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF ATDL-1 DATA LINK TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: ATDL-1 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF ATDL-1 DATA LINK TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: ATDL-1 SUPPORTING UNIT (SU) ADDRESS
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE USED AS AN ATDL-1 SUPPORTING UNIT (SU) ADDRESS.

Name: LINK 4 ADDRESS
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER APPLIED TO A LINK 4 INTERFACE UNIT TO ASSOCIATE INFORMATION AND DIRECTIVES WITH INTERFACE UNITS OR TRACKS FOR BOTH DIGITAL AND VOICE COMMUNICATIONS.

Name: LINK 4 ADDRESS BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF LINK 4 ADDRESSES.

Name: LINK 4 ADDRESS BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF LINK 4 ADDRESSES.

Name: LINK 11 11B TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: A 4-DIGIT OCTAL REFERENCE NUMBER FROM WITHIN THE FULL RANGE OF VALID LINK 11/11B TRACK NUMBERS. ALSO REFERRED TO AS A JTAO TRACK NUMBER.

Name: LINK 11 11B TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 4-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS WITHIN THE RANGE OF VALID LINK 11/11B SURVEILLANCE TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: LINK 11 11B TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 4-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS WITHIN THE RANGE OF VALID LINK 11/11B SURVEILLANCE TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: PARTICIPATING UNIT (PU) ADDRESS NUMBER
Explanation: A 2-DIGIT OCTAL IDENTIFIER FOR A UNIT COMMUNICATING DIRECTLY ON LINK 11.

Name: REPORTING UNIT (RU) ADDRESS NUMBER
Explanation: A 3-DIGIT OCTAL IDENTIFIER FOR A UNIT COMMUNICATING DIRECTLY ON LINK 11B.

Name: DISCRETE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE DISCRETE IDENTIFIER CODE IS A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER WHICH ASSISTS IN THE CORRELATION OF SHIPS AND AIRCRAFT REPORTED IN CHARACTER-ORIENTED MESSAGES WITH SHIPS AND AIRCRAFT REPORTED IN BIT-ORIENTED MESSAGES.

Name: LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER TO ASSIGN LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER OR ADDRESS WHOSE RANGES AND VALUES ARE DEFINED BY STANAG 5516.

Name: LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER REFERENCE FOR PRE-PLANNED TARGET
Explanation: THE UNIQUE LINK 16 IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO A PRE-PLANNED TARGET.

Name: ACM LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER REFERENCE
Explanation: THE UNIQUE LINK 16 IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO A SPECIFIC AIRSPACE CONTROL MEANS.

Name: UNDEFINED LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER REFERENCE
Explanation: THE UNIQUE LINK 16 IDENTIFIER THAT WILL BE ASSIGNED TO A FUTURE AIRSPACE CONTROL MEANS.

Name: LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS FROM WITHIN THE RANGE OF VALID LINK 16 SURVEILLANCE TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: LINK 16 TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS FROM WITHIN THE RANGE OF VALID LINK 16 SURVEILLANCE TRACK NUMBERS.

Name: PRIMARY JTIDS UNIT (JU) ADDRESS
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER REPRESENTING A PRIMARY JTIDS (JOINT TACTICAL INFORMATION DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM) UNIT ADDRESS.

Name: SECONDARY JTIDS UNIT (JU) ADDRESS
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER REPRESENTING A SECONDARY JTIDS (JOINT TACTICAL INFORMATION DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM) UNIT ADDRESS.

Name: JTIDS UNIT (JU) ADDRESS BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF LINK 16 ADDRESSES.

Name: JTIDS UNIT (JU) ADDRESS BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF LINK 16 ADDRESSES.

Name: IJMS TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, LOWER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL SYSTEM REFERENCE NUMBER (SRN) DENOTING THE LOWER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS FOR USE IN THE INTERIM JTIDS MESSAGE SPECIFICATION (IJMS).

Name: IJMS TRACK NUMBER BLOCK, UPPER LIMIT
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL SYSTEM REFERENCE NUMBER (SRN) DENOTING THE UPPER LIMIT OF A BLOCK OF TRACK NUMBERS FOR USE IN THE INTERIM JTIDS MESSAGE SPECIFICATION (IJMS).

Name: SUPPORTING UNIT (SU) NUMBER
Explanation: A 4-DIGIT OCTAL TRACK NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SUPPORTING UNIT IN A DATA LINK.

Name: JTIDS UNIT (JU) SOURCE TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: A 5-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER REPRESENTING THE JU SOURCE TRACK NUMBER ASSIGNED AS THE PRIMARY UNIT ADDRESS.
